# repos.conf — host-specific repository list
#
# One repository per line. Blank lines and comments (#) are ignored.
# Copy to "repos.conf" and adjust.
#
# Two line forms:
#   <name> = <url>   Named repository. The name (matching [A-Za-z0-9_-]+) lets an
#                    instance pick this repo via TARGET_REPOS in its *.conf file.
#   <url>            Bare URL. Its "name" defaults to the URL itself, so it can
#                    still be referenced verbatim by TARGET_REPOS.
# Names must be unique. restic URLs (rclone:/sftp:/s3:/paths) contain no "=", so
# a bare URL is never mistaken for a "<name> = <url>" line.
#
# ANY backend supported by restic works. rclone is optional — only targets with
# an "rclone:" prefix require rclone (and are checked for reachability
# beforehand via "rclone lsd"). Other backends are used directly.
#
# IMPORTANT: Multiple hosts must write to SEPARATE repositories. restic repos
# do not support simultaneous write access from multiple hosts.

# Tip: one repository name per host (e.g. restic-<host>) so that multiple hosts
# do not share the same repository.

# --- Local / externally mounted (no rclone needed) ---
local = /mnt/backup/restic-<host>
# /srv/backup/restic-<host>

# --- SFTP (no rclone needed) ---
# sftp = sftp:user@backup-host:/srv/restic-<host>

# --- S3 / compatible (no rclone needed; credentials via environment) ---
# s3 = s3:s3.amazonaws.com/bucket-name/restic-<host>

# --- Via rclone (rclone required, set up remote beforehand via "rclone config") ---
#
# CAUTION: The backup script runs as root, but "rclone config" is usually run as
# a normal user. Then the rclone.conf is in that user's home
# (~/.config/rclone/rclone.conf) and is NOT readable by root — the targets are
# then treated as "not reachable" and skipped. Remedy:
#   a) run "rclone config" as root straight away, OR
#   b) set RCLONE_CONFIG_FILE in global.conf to the absolute path of the
#      rclone.conf (e.g. /home/USER/.config/rclone/rclone.conf).
# The script checks this at startup and writes a corresponding note to the log.
# pcloud  = rclone:pcloud:restic-<host>
# hetzner = rclone:hetzner:restic-<host>
